    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn help menu:\r\n- If you open the table of contents (gO):\r\n    - quitting the table of contents window returns the cursor to the main window, rather than the help window\r\nfor nearly all cases, this is undesirable behavior, and makes little sense\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nwhen closing the table of contents window (opened with gO from the help docs), the cursor ought to return to the help window.\r\n\r\nThank you!",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This can be achieved using an autocommand:\r\n```vim\r\nfunc LocListLeave()\r\n  if win_gettype() == 'loclist'\r\n    call win_gotoid(getloclist(0, {'filewinid': 0}).filewinid)\r\n  endif\r\nendfunc\r\n\r\nautocmd WinLeave * call LocListLeave()\r\n```",
